.\" Manpage for kompex sqlite wrapper
.TH man 3 "14 April 2012" "1.0" "Kompex SQLite Wrapper man page"
.SH NAME
Kompex SQLite Wrapper \- an open source C++ wrapper library for SQLite.
.SH DESCRIPTION
The Kompex SQLite Wrapper is an open source C++ wrapper library for SQLite. 

The Wrapper wraps the SQLite C-functions and can be used on Windows and Linux operating systems.

It supports a wide range of SQLite functions and is up to date.

.SS Why should I use this wrapper?!
.IP
it is easy to use (see examples)

integral exception handling

transaction support

wide range of SQLite functions supported

std::count and std::cerr stream redirection

well documented

standard C++ source code (Linux and Windows portable)

wrapper can be used as shared or static library

database usage in memory

UTF-8 and UTF-16 support

.SH FILES
The header files are located in {headerdir} directory.

The library is available both as shared object and static library:
.IP
{libdir}/{PRODUCT_NAME}.a
.br
{libdir}/{PRODUCT_NAME}.so

.SH SEE ALSO
The online documentation can be found at:
.IP
http://sqlitewrapper.kompex-online.com/index.php?content=documentation

